[30;1m165 | [0m[35m      \ is to use free-form text fields, such as would appear in sentences or paragraphs\[0m
[30;1m166 | [0m[35m      \ from a Methods section. Metadata fields are text to enable them to be more\[0m

[30;1m255 | [0m[35m# ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^[0m

[30;1m699 | [0m[35m#[0m
[30;1m700 | [0m[35m# In the above cases we used the built-in capabilities of PyNWB to perform iterative data write. To[0m
[30;1m701 | [0m[35m# gain more fine-grained control of the write process we can alternatively use PyNWB to setup the fu[0m
[30;1m702 | [0m[35m# structure of our NWB file and then update select datasets afterwards. This approach is useful, e.g[0m

[30;1m32 | [0m[35me when dealing with large data arrays is that it is often[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35m#   not feasible to load all of the data into memory. Using an iterative data write process allows u[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35m#   to avoid this problem by writing the data one-subblock-at-a-time, so that we only need to hold[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m#   a small subset of the array in memory at any given time.[0m
[30;1m36 | [0m[35m# * **Data streaming** In the context of streaming data we are faced with several issues:[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35m#   **1)** data is not available in-memory but arrives in subblocks as the stream progresses[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35m#   **2)** caching the data of a stream in-memory is often prohibitively expensive and volatile[0m

[30;1m141 | [0m[35m# Each :py:class:`~pynwb.file.NWBFile` must have a session description, identifier, and session star[0m
[30;1m142 | [0m[35m# Importantly, the session start time is the reference time for all timestamps in the file.[0m
[30;1m143 | [0m[35m# For instance, an event with a timestamp of 0 in the file means the event[0m
[30;1m144 | [0m[35m# occurred exactly at the session start time.[0m

[30;1m703 | [0m[35m   Overview of the data structure for storing spiking unit data and metadata in NWB 2.0.[0m
[30;1m704 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m705 | [0m[35mIn addition to ``spike_times``, the units table includes the following optional columns:[0m

[30;1m707 | [0m[35m   - ``electrodes``: range references to the electrodes table indicating which electrodes from which[0m

[30;1m709 | [0m[35m   - ``waveform_mean``: mean waveform across all recorded spikes.[0m
